1. e4 c5 2. Nc3
{ Hello dear readers!  Since this course is big enough and not all of you will have time to study everything completely, I have decided to consider in this chapter Quickstarter guide the main, most popular variations. I have selected 13 of the most common variations that will allow you to start playing Closed Sicilian without deeply studying the entire course.   I hope the Quickstarter guide will help you get started using the Closed Sicilian in your games, and after studying it, you will be tempted to study some of the variations in more detail. }
