[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Quickstarter guide"]
[Black "2. ... d6 "]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nc3 d6 3. g3 Nf6 4. Bg2 e6 5. d3 Be7 6. f4 Nbd7
{ Only this move has a value. Although the Knight on d7 is placed much worse than on c6. }
7. Nf3 a6 { Black's main plan remains unchanged - an attack on the queenside. }
8. O-O O-O 9. a4 { Useful prophylaxis against ...b5. } 9... Qc7 10. Qe2
{ We are not only developing the Queen but also preparing the advance of the e-pawn. }
10... Rb8 11. e5
{ Capturing space in the center and forcing the Black Knight to worsen its position. }
11... Ne8 12. a5 { Grabbing space across the board and preventing ... b5. }
12... b6 13. axb6 Qxb6
{ Black's queenside pawn structure has become more broken thanks to the move a5. }
14. Kh1
{ Moving away from a potential discovered check along the b6-g1 diagonal. The position of White is better due to the poor placing of Black pieces, almost all of them are on the penultimate and last rank, and White has the advantage in space. }
