15... Bd7 16. Rab1 { Preparing b2-b4 } 16... b5 17. b4
{ Temporarily sacrificing a pawn. } 17... Qxa3 18. Nxd4 cxd4 19. Ne2
{ And Black has no good way to protect the d4 pawn. } 19... Qa6 20. Nxd4
{ It’s important not to forget to eat pawns! } 20... Qb6
{ Our Knight is pinned but can be easily defended. } 21. c3 Nc6 22. Qf2
{ White is slightly better due to the more solid pawn structure, the bad pawn on d6 and the exposed Black King. }
