{ The natural but dangerous decision. The Bishop on g4 is almost trapped. } 16.
Nf2 Bh5 17. Nb3 { Improving the position of the Knight. } 17... O-O 18. Nh1
{ The amazing move! Just imagine your opponent's face if you manage to play this move in the game. The idea is to transfer the Knight to g3 and attack the Bishop on h5. }
18... f5 19. Ng3 a5 20. Nxh5 gxh5 21. Rad1
{ Black's pawn structure is awful and White has the clear plan of advancing the d-pawn. }
