8... Re8
{ With the idea to play ...Bh8 after Bh6. But I think this move is just a mistake. The threat of exchanging dark-squared Bishops is not so scary as to spend a whole tempo to avoid it. }
9. Nge2 Rb8 10. O-O { Now we are starting our typical plan on the kingside. }
10... b5 11. f4 b4 12. Nd1 Qc7 13. g4
{ With the idea to transfer the Knight on g3 and push f-pawn. } 13... e6 14. a3
{ And again useful inclusion! Without making a single move, the Rook becomes active. }
14... a5 15. axb4 axb4 16. f5
{ And we have the choice to either close the kingside with g5 and f6 or hold the tension with Bh6 or Bg5. }
