12... Bb7 13. axb4 axb4 14. f4
{ Starting a typical plan to advance a pawn to f5. } 14... Nd7 15. f5
{ Objectively, the position is approximately equal, but I would prefer White because of the clear attack on the kingside. White is going to play Bh6, Nf2 and Ng4. }
