13... Rae8 14. Bh6 { With the idea to exchange the strong Bishop. } 14... f6
15. Raf1
{ Doubling the Rooks on the f-file. Before starting an active play, we improve the position of all the pieces. }
15... b5 16. e5
{ This interesting sacrifice requires accurate play from both players. } 16...
dxe5 17. Ne4
{ This interesting sacrifice requires accurate play from both players. } 17...
Bxh6 18. Qxh6 Nef5
{ It seems that it's the most logical move in the position. Black improves the passive Knight and leaves the other in the center. But the Knight on d4 is too vulnerable. }
19. Nxf5 { There is no longer a need for sacrifices. } 19... Nxf5
