{ The idea of ​​early capture on f4 is very simple: to open the a1-h8 diagonal for the Black dark-squared Bishop. But this decision also has some drawbacks. Firstly, Black trades the central pawn for a side pawn. Secondly, White's dark-squared bishop also becomes more active. And finally, thirdly, the open f-file is more of a plus for White than for Black. }
