7. Qd2 Qa5 8. f4
{ Since White can't play the typical move Bh6 in these positions in the near future, we play f4! An active move that will allow us to develop the Knight to f3. }
8... Rb8 9. Nf3 e6 10. e5
{ Novelty! Until the Black pieces are developed, we want to open the center as much as possible. }
10... dxe5 11. fxe5 Nxf3+ 12. Bxf3 Bxe5 13. Bf4
{ It's a good idea to exchange a defender of the weak dark squares created by the pawns all being on light squares. Furthermore, the Black Bishop is the only active minor piece. }
13... Bxf4 14. Qxf4
{ When you sacrifice a material, it's very important to play forcingly and not give your opponent a break. }
14... Ra8 15. O-O Ne7 16. Ne4
{ Threatening to play either Nf6 or Nd6. Black's position is hopeless. } *

