10. Bxc5 { I find the c5-pawn more important than the b2-pawn. } 10... d6
{ Otherwise White will occupy the d6-square with the Bishop, and it will be very difficult for Black to untie himself. }
11. Ba3 { It is important to keep the pressure on the a3-f8 diagonal. } 11...
Ne7 12. O-O O-O 13. Qd2 { Threatening to attack the d6 pawn with Qb4. } 13...
Qc7
{ The c2-pawn is under the gun now and Black intends to defend his pawn by Rd8. }
14. c4 { Great move! We're grabbing the space in the center. } 14... Rb8 15.
Rfc1
{ When your pieces are better placed, open a position! Therefore, our plan is to advance c5. }
