O-O 11. O-O h6 12. Bxf6
{ Of course, we don't want to retreat back with the Bishop after ... h6. }
12... Bxf6 13. Rad1
{ The most natural and strongest move. Black can no longer defend the d5-pawn. }
13... Qe7
{ A small trap. It is important not to capture the d5-pawn with the Knight because the Knight on e2 is left unprotected. }
14. Bxd5 Bxd5 15. Rxd5
{ Followed by doubling of the Rooks along the d-file. Black has insufficient compensation for the pawn. }
