{ This move is often used by players whose main weapon against the Open Sicilian is the Najdorf variation.   3.Nf3  d6  4.d4  cxd4  5.Nxd4  is a transposition to the main line of Najdorf. The main idea of ​​the move ...a6 is to advance the b-pawn as soon as possible and create pressure on the important e-pawn. }
3. g3
{ As before, we're intending to develop the Bishop on the important diagonal h1-a8. }
3... b5 4. Bg2 Bb7 5. d3
{ We are playing the Closed Sicilian, so we're closing the game with d3. White could continue either with Nge2 or open the game with d4. }
5... e6 6. Nh3
{ Quite rare, but a very interesting move. The main idea is to keep the d1-h5 diagonal open for the Queen on d1. In addition, White has better control over the d5-square and has the opportunity to transfer the Knight to f4 or g5. I think this variation is a great finding for the Closed Sicilian player. }
